House Price Prediction – Project Summary
Student Details

Name: Arnav Singh
College: Graphic Era Deemed to be University

Project Objective

The objective of this project was to develop a machine learning model capable of predicting house prices based on various property features such as area, number of bedrooms, bathrooms, parking availability, and location-related attributes. The project aimed to assist buyers and sellers in estimating fair property values using data-driven insights.

Dataset

The Housing Prices Dataset was obtained from Kaggle and contains information about residential properties, including physical characteristics and amenities. The dataset was cleaned and preprocessed before model training.

Methodology
Loaded and explored the dataset using Pandas.
Removed duplicate records and handled missing values.
Converted categorical variables into numerical form using one-hot encoding.
Split the data into training (80%) and testing (20%) sets.
Trained two regression models:
Linear Regression
Random Forest Regressor
Evaluated performance using MAE, RMSE, and R² Score.
Key Findings
House area was one of the strongest factors influencing price.
Features such as bathrooms, parking spaces, air conditioning, and preferred area also significantly impacted property values.
Random Forest Regressor achieved better prediction accuracy than Linear Regression.
The model was able to predict house prices with good accuracy and can be useful for real estate decision-making.
Recommendation

Real estate businesses should focus on property size, location quality, and essential amenities when pricing houses. Machine learning models can support more accurate and consistent pricing strategies
